    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Chess\" title=\"Chess\">Chess</a> * <a href=\"/Squares\" title=\"Squares\">Squares</a> * Intersection Squares</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://www.mcescher.com/Gallery/back-bmp/LW377.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/77/Two_Intersecting_Planes.jpg/300px-Two_Intersecting_Planes.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"227\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/7/77/Two_Intersecting_Planes.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Two_Intersecting_Planes.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/Category:M._C._Escher\" title=\"Category:M. C. Escher\">M. C. Escher</a> - Two Intersecting Planes, 1952 <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Intersection squares</b> are the result of the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line-line_intersection\">intersection of two lines</a> from two different squares with two disjoint directions, either <a href=\"/Ranks\" title=\"Ranks\">rank</a>, <a href=\"/Files\" title=\"Files\">file</a>, <a href=\"/Diagonals\" title=\"Diagonals\">diagonal</a> or <a href=\"/Anti-Diagonals\" title=\"Anti-Diagonals\">anti-diagonal</a>, in total 2*(3+2+1) = 12 possible combinations. Those lines (may) have up to one square, where both lines intersect - a square where two appropriate sliding pieces were able to move to in one step (assuming no obstructions).\n</p><p>In the set-wise world of <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">bitboards</a> one usually relies on <a href=\"/General_Setwise_Operations#Intersection\" title=\"General Setwise Operations\">set-wise intersection</a> of <a href=\"/Sliding_Piece_Attacks\" title=\"Sliding Piece Attacks\">sliding piece attacks</a>, but square-centric <a href=\"/Board_Representation\" title=\"Board Representation\">board representations</a> may either use two-dimensional lookup tables, or rely on some algebra based on discrete <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_equation\">linear equations</a> and pure register computation. Programs may use these routines as a precondition whether an intersection point exist, for instance to determine a square where a sliding piece may check the opponent king. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Rank_and_File\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rank and File</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Empty_Intersection_with_0x88_Math\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Empty Intersection with 0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Rank_and_Diagonal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rank and Diagonal</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#0x88_Math\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#C-Source\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">C-Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#File_and_Diagonal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">File and Diagonal</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#0x88_Math_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#C-Source_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">C-Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Rank_and_Anti-Diagonal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rank and Anti-Diagonal</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#0x88_Math_3\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#C-Source_3\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">C-Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#File_and_Anti-Diagonal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">File and Anti-Diagonal</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#0x88_Math_4\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#C-Source_4\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">C-Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#Diagonal_and_Anti-Diagonal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Diagonal and Anti-Diagonal</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-16\"><a href=\"#0x88_Math_5\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">0x88 Math</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-17\"><a href=\"#C-Source_5\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">C-Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-18\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-19\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">9</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-20\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">10</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rank_and_File\">Rank and File</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Rank and File\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>or vice versa File and Rank\n</p><p>Two squares a and b have always two orthogonal intersection squares s1 and s2. \n</p>\n<pre>\n. | . . . | . .\n--1-------b----\n. | . . . | . .\n. | . . . | . .\n. | . . . | . .\n. | . . . | . .\n--a-------2----\n. | . . . | . .\n</pre>\n<pre>\ns1&#160;:= 8*rankIndex(b) + fileIndex(a);\ns2&#160;:= 8*rankIndex(a) + fileIndex(b);\n</pre>\n<p>or\n</p>\n<pre>\ns1&#160;:= (b &amp; 56) + (a &amp; 7);\ns2&#160;:= (a &amp; 56) + (b &amp; 7);\n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Empty_Intersection_with_0x88_Math\">Empty Intersection with 0x88 Math</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Empty Intersection with 0x88 Math\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>If diagonals or anti-diagonals are involved, the intersection square may off the board. Beside that, the intersection of a diagonal with an anti-diagonal becomes empty, if both lines are of different <a href=\"/Color_of_a_Square\" title=\"Color of a Square\">square color</a>. Considering <a href=\"/0x88\" title=\"0x88\">0x88</a>-square coordinates for the calculation, covers off the board intersection, and the different color issues en passant. Following <a href=\"/C\" title=\"C\">C</a>-routines work branchless, and return -1 if no intersection is possible by oring with following {0,-1} integer expression relying on arithmetical shift right:\n</p>\n<pre>\n -(s88 &amp; 0x88) &gt;&gt; (sizeof(int)-1)\n</pre>\n<p>Feel free to use branches instead in a broader scope, since one need to branch on valid intersecion square anyway.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rank_and_Diagonal\">Rank and Diagonal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Rank and Diagonal\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>or vice versa Diagonal and Rank\n</p>\n<pre>\n. . . . . . / .\n. . . . . b . .\n. . . . / . . .\n. . . / . . . .\n. . / . . . . .\n. / . . . . . .\ns-----a--------\n. . . . . . . .\n</pre>\n<p>with\n</p>\n<pre>diagonalIndex&#160;:= rankIndex - fileIndex;\n</pre>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> r/f\n</th>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<th> 5\n</th>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<th> 7\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 7\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 7\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 5\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -6\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -7\n</td></tr></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"0x88_Math\">0x88 Math</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 0x88 Math\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<pre>\nrankIndex(s)&#160;:= rankIndex(a);\nfileIndex(s)&#160;:= rankIndex(s) - diagonalIndex(s);\nfileIndex(s)&#160;:= rankIndex(a) - rankIndex(b) + fileIndex(b);\n</pre>\n<p>Because the intersection of any rank with any diagonal may off the board, we rely on 0x88 math for a quick test:\n</p>\n<pre>\ns88&#160;:= 16*rankIndex(s) + fileIndex(s);\ns88&#160;:= 16*rankIndex(a) + (rankIndex(a) - rankIndex(b) + fileIndex(b));\ns88&#160;:= 17*rankIndex(a) -  rankIndex(b) + fileIndex(b);\nif ( s88 &amp; 0x88)\n   intersection off board;\nelse\n   sq&#160;:= ((sq88 &gt;&gt; 1) &amp; 56) + (sq88 &amp; 7);\n</pre>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"C-Source\">C-Source</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: C-Source\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<pre>\n/****************************************\n * return: intersection square (if any)\n *          of rank of square a\n *          with diagonal of square b\n *         -1 if no intersection exists\n ****************************************/\nint intersectRankDia(int a, int b) {\n   int s88 = 17*(a&gt;&gt;3) - (b &gt;&gt; 3) + (b &amp; 7);\n   return (((s88 &gt;&gt; 1) &amp; 56) + (s88 &amp; 7)) | ( -(s88 &amp; 0x88) &gt;&gt; 31);\n}\n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"File_and_Diagonal\">File and Diagonal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: File and Diagonal\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>or vice versa Diagonal and File\n</p>\n<pre>\n. . . | . . / .\n. . . | . b . .\n. . . | / . . .\n. . . s . . . .\n. . / | . . . .\n. / . | . . . .\n/ . . a . . . .\n. . . | . . . .\n</pre>\n<p>with\n</p>\n<pre>diagonalIndex&#160;:= rankIndex - fileIndex;\n</pre>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> r/f\n</th>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<th> 5\n</th>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<th> 7\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 7\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 7\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 5\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -6\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -3\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -4\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -5\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -6\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -7\n</td></tr></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"0x88_Math_2\">0x88 Math</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 0x88 Math\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<pre>\nfileIndex(s)&#160;:= fileIndex(a);\nrankIndex(s)&#160;:= fileIndex(s) + diagonalIndex(s);\nrankIndex(s)&#160;:= fileIndex(a) + rankIndex(b) - fileIndex(b);\n</pre>\n<p>Because the intersection of any file with any diagonal may off the board, we rely on 0x88 math for a quick test:\n</p>\n<pre>\ns88&#160;:= 16*rankIndex(s) + fileIndex(s);\ns88&#160;:= 16*(fileIndex(a) + rankIndex(b) - fileIndex(b)) + fileIndex(a);\ns88&#160;:= 17*fileIndex(a) + 16*rankIndex(b) - 16*fileIndex(b);\nif ( s88 &amp; 0x88)\n   intersection off board;\nelse\n   sq&#160;:= ((sq88 &gt;&gt; 1) &amp; 56) + (sq88 &amp; 7);\n</pre>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"C-Source_2\">C-Source</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: C-Source\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<pre>\n/****************************************\n * return: intersection square (if any)\n *          of file of square a\n *          with diagonal of square b\n *         -1 if no intersection exists\n ****************************************/\nint intersectFileDia(int a, int b) {\n   int s88 = 17*(a &amp; 7) + 2*(b &amp; 56) - 16*(b &amp; 7);\n   return (((s88 &gt;&gt; 1) &amp; 56) + (s88 &amp; 7)) | ( -(s88 &amp; 0x88) &gt;&gt; 31);\n}\n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rank_and_Anti-Diagonal\">Rank and Anti-Diagonal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Intersection_Squares&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Rank and Anti-Diagonal\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>or vice versa Anti-Diagonal and Rank\n</p>\n<pre>\n. . . . . . . .\n. . . . . . . .\n\\ . . . . . . .\n. b . . . . . .\n. . \\ . . . . .\n. . . \\ . . . .\n------a-s------\n. . . . . \\ . .\n</pre>\n<p>with\n</p>\n<pre>antidiagIndex&#160;:= rankIndex + fileIndex;\n</pre>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> r/f\n</th>\n<th> 0\n</th>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<th> 5\n</th>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<th> 7\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 7\n</th>\n<th> 7\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 8\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 9\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 10\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 11\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 12\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 13\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 14\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 6\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 6\n</td>\n<th> 7\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 8\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 9\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 10\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 11\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 12\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 13\n</td>